PROREMA Branding Customization Guide

Overview

1. Brand Color
2. Typography
3. Company Logo


--- 1. Company Brand Color ---

PROREMA's Characteristic Color is Lima Green (#00b04e). It is used for main Links, primary Buttons and several backgrounds.
It can be changed in any color (recommended: green, blue, dark orange).

- Go to main/resources/static/css/ and open "bootstrap.min.css".
- Find every "00b04e" element and change it into the prefered color


--- 2. Typography ---

PROREMA uses "Montserrat" by Julieta Ulanovsky. It is embedded online via Google's Font Service:
https://www.google.com/fonts#UsePlace:use/Collection:Montserrat

- Go to main/resources/static/css/
To change the font into the companys font, import the new font into the head of the following css files:
bootstrap.min.css; style.css
Example: @import url(https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Montserrat:400,700);

Then replace every mention of "Montserrat" into the name of your font. Resize the font on your demand.


--- 3. Company Logo ---

- Go to main/resources/static/img/ and open "bootstrap.min.css".
Replace the following images with your branded images:

Login Page Logo: prorema.png (738x209px)
Top Left Logo: prorema_small.png (250x64px)

